The fraction of RNA cleaved in each band under a specific theophylline concentration was calculated from the difference between sample intensity and minimum intensity divided by the difference between maximum intensity and minimum intensity. The maximum and minimum intensities are the highest and lowest values measured for each nucleotide position over a range of theophylline concentrations. The value of the fraction of RNA cleaved and logarithm of theophylline concentrations were plotted and fitted to a logistic dose-response model according to the following equation (28,29).
